                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Good news looks like they Fixed the problem with the charmed pet not being able to be buffed due to the message "Target not Grouped" I've now been successful in buffing my pets with Haste, Hate, damage shield and even clarity, and I imagine they they receive all the current group buffs when they become charmed too <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> this is great news.
<br />

<br />
However I found another bug. When using a charmed mob to solo and it is sent it to engage another mob and when it is able to hold aggro what happens is that when charm breaks the mobs continue fighting, so if you don't re-charm your pet and it lands a hit on the mob you are fighting while un-charmed then they both become no-loot and the encounter is wasted.. so I'm still trying to tweak re-charming combos with stuns in order to prevent this from happening. As of now I'm just clicking the charm button like a mad man when the timer is close to expiration so I can get the charm off before the mob swings again. Currently I'm soloing in Everfrost @ level 46, charming lvl 49 bears and mowing down solo giants faster then most groups. If I throw in 2 nukes I can drop a mob long before my pets charm breaks and the xp is great, around 0.4 a kill whereas in a group of 6 in permafrost killing the highest level mobs in the place I was only getting 0.1 a kill. There is truly a lack of high level xp content in the game right now, no xp mobs above level 50, so imagine @ lvl 49 being forced to fight 90% blue con's in a full party it will take ages to level up. Solo is the way to go lvl 45+ for xp as long as you have the capabilities. Also a duo combo with a summoner has been my best small group experience yet, they can get their pet to hold aggro while you get your charmed pet to pound down the mob. Having their pet hold aggro will prevent the no-loot problem too so mistakes on re-casting charm will be less costly. 
<br />

<br />
Anyways.. has anyone else used this spell yet or experimented?? I'm still using the app 4 version and it terms of duration and resist I haven't run into any major problems yet but Id like to hear from everyone. 
<br />

<br />
Kothar Magistic - 46 Coercer - Befallen</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
